headline: This High-Yield Dividend Stock Is Beaten Down, But Wall Street Still Loves It
summary: AT&T was upgraded to "Overweight" by KeyBanc on Nov. 12, with a $30 price target, after a recent selloff and rising wireless competition, based on analyst confidence in strong fiber growth, resilient earnings, and attractive dividend yield.
